Description: 
Two silvertip sharks must be flown 6,000 miles from 
Australia to Dubai for a breeding programme, but the 
animals are extremely hard to keep alive in confined 
spaces. Specialist animal movers construct a water tank 
and reinforce the aircraft to keep them alive en route, 
but the journey remains very dangerous as any delay in 
the 30-hour trip could mean the oxygen inside the tank 
runs out.
